HEADWORD: Goudron
<hw>Gou`dron"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F., tar.]</ety>
<fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>a small fascine or fagot, steeped in wax, pitch,
and glue, used in various ways, as for igniting buildings or works, or
to light ditches and ramparts.</def> <rj><au>Farrow.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

